cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the design of a low-latency control plane for LTE networks. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper discusses the efficient transmission and reception of control plane messages over the LTE spectrum, cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper discusses the benefits of SwiftC in implementing complex interference management techniques, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper may discuss security concerns related to the low-latency control plane design, and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper discusses the coordination signaling link between small cells and the macrocell.
